Package uk.co.codera.lang.concurrent

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Command
    A command is simply a request to do something.
    CommandExecutor
    Indicates that this task wraps a command and will execute the command when it is invoked.
    Task
    Tasks are the mechanism used to execute commands Command using the PriorityTaskExecutor.
    TaskCallback
    Callback interface used to notify clients about various aspects of the task lifecycle such as whether a task has been executed or cancelled.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    PriorityTaskExecutor
    A task executor that will process tasks in priority order.
    PriorityTaskExecutor.Builder  
    SequencedPriorityExecutor
    An implementation of the Executor that is backed by a PriorityBlockingQueue.
    TaskCallbackAdapter
    Implementation of the TaskCallback where all the methods have a do nothing implementation.
    Tasks
    Responsible for constructing the different kind of tasks used by the PriorityTaskExecutor.
    Tasks.AbstractCorrelatedTask  
    Tasks.AbstractCorrelatedTask.Builder<T>  
    Tasks.AbstractTask  
    Tasks.AbstractTask.Builder<T>  
    Tasks.CancellableTask
    This kind of task can be cancelled by a Tasks.CancellingTask that has the same correlationId and a sequence that is considered later than that on this task.
    Tasks.CancellableTask.Builder  
    Tasks.CancellingTask
    This kind of task will cancel any Tasks.CancellableTask that has the same correlationId and an earlier sequence to this task.
    Tasks.CancellingTask.Builder  
    Tasks.SimpleTask
    This is the default kind of task.
    Tasks.SimpleTask.Builder
